UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2051
1 AN ACT relating to the establishment of a Medicaid state-directed payment
2 program.
3 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
4 Section 1. KRS 205.6412 is amended to read as follows:
5 To the extent permitted under federal law and in addition to, and separate from, the
6 programs developed pursuant to KRS 205.6406, the department shall develop
7 programs[a program] to improve quality of and access to care for residents of the
8 Commonwealth enrolled in the state's Medicaid program by increasing Medicaid
9 reimbursement rates for qualifying hospitals in accordance with the following:
10 (1) (a) A qualifying hospital shall be eligible to earn enhanced add-on payments from
11 Medicaid managed care organizations based on the qualifying hospital's
12 average commercial rate for services provided, including but not limited to
13 inpatient hospital services, outpatient hospital services, and professional
14 services, if the qualifying hospital:
15 1. a. Is a participant in the hospital rate improvement program
16 developed pursuant to KRS 205.6406;
17 b. Is a Level II, III, or IV trauma center;
18 c. Is located in a county in which the percentage of the county's
19 population enrolled in the state's Medicaid program exceeds the
20 statewide median Medicaid enrollment percentage for all counties
21 as posted by the Cabinet for Health and Family Services in the
22 December edition of the Monthly Medicaid Counts by County
23 report for the calendar year preceding the year in which the
24 preprint is submitted; and
25 d. Has an agreement for clinical rotations to train providers with a
26 university-affiliated graduate medical education program; or
27 2. Is a pediatric teaching hospital as defined in KRS 205.565, except that a
Page 1 of 4
