UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2051
1 hospital qualifying for enhanced add-on payments under this
2 subparagraph shall only be eligible to receive enhanced add-on
3 payments for services delivered to a patient who is eighteen (18) years
4 of age or younger;
5 (2) (a) Within sixty (60) days after the effective date of this Act, the Department for
6 Medicaid Services shall submit a Medicaid preprint with a January 1, 2026,
7 effective date to the federal Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services
8 seeking authorization to implement the state-directed payment program
9 described in this subsection.
10 (b) If the preprint required to be submitted under paragraph (a) of this
11 subsection is approved by the federal Centers for Medicare and Medicaid
12 Services, a qualifying hospital shall be eligible to earn enhanced add-on
13 payments from Medicaid managed care organizations based on the
14 equivalent Medicare rate for services, including but not limited to physician
15 and nonphysician professional services, provided to Medicaid beneficiaries
16 by the qualifying hospital's affiliated physician groups or physicians or
17 other professionals employed by or contracted with the qualifying hospital if
18 the qualifying hospital has an agreement to train providers with a state-
19 owned university-affiliated graduate medical education program;
20 (3) For state-directed payments authorized under this section:
21 (a)[(b)] There shall be an identified source of funding, which shall be separate
22 from the assessment authorized in KRS 205.6406 and shall not be from the
23 general fund, for the nonfederal share that is in compliance with the
24 requirements of the United States Centers for Medicare and Medicaid
25 Services;
26 (b)[(c)] A qualifying hospital shall be required to report the same quality
27 measures as are applicable under:
Page 2 of 4
