UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2051
1 1. The state university teaching hospital Medicaid directed payment plan
2 for the payment program authorized under subsection (1) of this
3 section; and
4 2. Similarly approved payment programs active in the Commonwealth
5 for the payment program authorized under subsection (2) of this
6 section; and
7 (c)[(d)] Reimbursement for qualifying hospitals under this section shall only
8 apply to patients covered by a Medicaid managed care organization;[.]
9 (4)[(2)] The state-directed[ directed payment programs[program] authorized under
10 this section shall be separate and distinct from any state-directed[ directed] payment
11 program authorized under KRS 205.6406, and the department shall only implement
12 the program described in this section if:
13 (a) Medicaid documentation required for federal financial participation is
14 approved by the United States Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services;
15 and
16 (b) The United States Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services agrees to
17 consider the program through its own preprint and without affecting or
18 altering any other state-directed[ directed] payment program; and[.]
19 (5)[(3)] The department shall promulgate administrative regulations in accordance
20 with KRS Chapter 13A to implement the programs[program] described in this
21 section.
22 Section 2. If the Medicaid preprint required to be submitted under subsection
23 (2) of Section 1 of this Act is approved by the federal Centers for Medicaid and Medicare
24 Services with a retroactive effective date of January 1, 2026, the Department for
25 Medicaid Services shall, upon receipt of approval from the federal Centers for Medicare
26 and Medicaid Services, direct each Medicaid managed care organization with which the
27 department has contracted for delivery of Medicaid services to make retroactive
